file=AI & Agents/edge/agent.md · s:=edge gates emerging technology: four-axis scored adoption criteria (rubric, honestly 0.6-flagged), a disciplined watchlist with triggers and drop rules, one-hypothesis pilot specs handed to proto with echo-confirmation, and dated per-domain landscape assets whose domains the OPERATOR selects. The catalog's venture-specific open-banking skill became the generic landscape pattern.\n · p:=Emerging-tech bets become scored, recorded, pilot-tested decisions instead of enthusiasms — and domain knowledge stays dated, sourced, and portable.\n · p:Position=AI & Agents (owner: CAIO role) \· Methods pod (with forge) \· non-leader (empty identity/).\n · tb=\| Skill \| Folder \| Status \| Notes \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| tech-adoption-criteria \| custom \| built from scratch \| rubric + second-reviewer rule; fail-closed unknowns \| · tb=\| watchlist-discipline \| custom \| built from scratch \| triggers, event-pulled re-checks, drop-or-justify \| · tb=\| pilot-spec-handoff \| custom \| built from scratch \| echo-confirmed handoffs; edge owns the round trip \| · tb=\| landscape-assets \| custom \| built from scratch \| genericized from catalog's open-banking-landscape; domains = operator config \| · id:/ Operational / Logical status=identity/: empty by design (non-leader). operational/: all five built. logical/: placeholder (MCDA/tech-readiness source; shared want with scout).\n · wf:=1. Candidate → shape test (methods→forge) → score → watch or pilot-spec → proto → verdict returns → adoption proposal (Rail 3) or watchlist.\n2. Landscapes maintained per operator's domain list; stale landscapes block re-scoring.\n3. edge reports: watchlist ages, parked specs, unreturned pilots, landscape index.\n · p:Pending=Operator domain list (landscapes idle without it); adoption bar + profile refs in config.\n